column5: Was out this morning on Cooks, scored 5 pike, biggest one was 32 inches. Pretty good day.
Sounds like you had an Awesome Time....Nice Pics !
Did you just troll for those jacks or still fish
I just drift with the wind and cast, making a few passes.
That is how I usually fish for them too. I have been on a dry spell for pike on Cook`s all this year. At least there is a steady supply of aggressive perch to continually entertain.
Nice long fish, not very fat though considering winter's coming up.
